reviews.text: Joy Homestead is a historical site on the W3R heritage route.  Open June 18th at 6pm to celebrate the March of the French soldiers on June 18th 1781.  Tea and Strawberry biscuits served. 5.00 donation.  Wear your best colonial outfit or uniform
Remarkably preserved colonial-era home, wonderful tour by historian who knew her history.
A quaint 18th century, pre-revolution home.
Square dancing at the grange... swinging squares.  Awesome group uses the wonderful old Grange.  Lovely building with fine memorabilia.  It is an active Grange.  Lovely!
Before got too cold to go sit outside we had a very nice picnic ads are Oakland Grange we know the person who actually run some place and we went to a picnic with enjoyed ourselves nice time
Clean, good appointments, welcoming and we had a good time there.
Good place for a small event
This older building is very well cared for and maintained my Buddhist group has their monthly meetings here and it's very pleasant
Step back in time in this 18th Century museum, perfectly furnished in period antiques.  Call for tour appointment and hear about Rhode Island's industrial revolution and the Sprague family dynasty.

It will take you back to an easier time. Right across the street is the Cranston print works. All textiles in one location. As you cross the street, look down to the right. You will go back in time. All the mill workers were housed there. When you see the ones with 2 doors those were the workers houses. The single door ones were for the supervisors. The mansion is all in time of the era. Trust me, its an experience you will remember. Oh by the way, the kids love the mansion!! And the needle crafts are insane!!! I hope you love it all. Please share your experience with family and friends. Tell others.
Interesting story and holds a big part of Rhode Island history. The people that give the tours are very passionate and sweet.
Fine 19th century architecture!
Very charming mansion, nicely decorated for different holidays, a real gem to behold ! Must stop in!
This is the quintessential Rhode island breakfast joint. Food is good and the portions are big, but what really makes it special are the people who work here.  They are so sweet and funny.

I was craving something fluffy and sweet but not too fat— behold the patriot waffle! I thought it was ‘Belgian’ but turns out I was wrong... anyways, this little baby right here turned out to be the best thing I ate all day (I mean yeah it was morning) TRULY LOVED IT. Great and fast service too! BTW TOTALLY LOVE THE PRICES. loved my experience. and my waffle. ^ v ^

Generous portions and good coffee. Whether you like it is going to depend on how you like things cooked. I am not a fan of scramble type omelets,  but if you are,  it's all good.  The ham steak is HUGE and they don't scrimp on other meats. Friendly service.

Their servings are massive and their prices are fair. For under 10$ I got a piece of ham, 2 slices of bacon, 2 eggs, one long sausage link, a heaping pile of home fries and french toast. Everything was cooked beautifully. The eggs weren't runny and the bacon was perfectly crisp. The home fries were slightly overseasoned but this didn't detract from my enjoyement of the meal. This diner really is a must visit, highly recommend!
Great place for breakfast. They can stay very busy all morning but still turn over pretty fast. I've never waited more than 15 minutes. Friendly staff and gigantic muffins can be found at Athena's

Go here more often than I should! My friend loves their pizza slices & I prefer the calzone..call ahead & your calzone is made to order...when my sister visits, she always picks up some tiramisu before she heads back out of state. I love the mini cannollis!
Plenty of calzone selections. Sicilian style pizza is a great deal for a party. They sell regular and multi grain pizza dough.
Great prices. Great calzones!
MEATBALL PIES WITH CHEESE AFFORDABILITY AND WORLD CLASS SERVICE AND TASTE !!

Ordered a small pizza and paids for it.was told it would be about half hour. Asked where I sould wait and wastold anywhere. Sat at a table close by. Got up to  check on my after about 25 .minutes and was told I wasn't waiting in the right place. When my order  came out on time they asked me to pay again. This action was not done in a very friendly manner. I don't know if I will ever return. The pizza itself was alright
A tasty refreshing treat for a hot summer day. "Real Rhode Islanders" don't use a spoon or a straw. That explains why I'm surrounded by numbskulls. Y'all got brain freeze!
It's  DEL's...what more needs to be said? RI thing....you understand,  right?
Great! A Rhode Island tradition!

This place is a Rhode island tradition.   If you are visiting here you must try it.  Just dont use a straw, as it sucks all the juice out and leaves just ice.  Many flavors to choose from. I perfor classic lemon which includes Chunks of actual lemon.  They also have candy, nachos and pretzels.  Definitely worth finding 1.

While the bottled drink is exceptional, either regular or pink lemonade, in looking for something to give to your guests who may be traveling from afar their individual packets are the way to go. 

As part of our Rhode Island themed welcome wedding bags, the Del's lemonade packets were perfect to showcase what is truly unique from our little Rhody. 

A quick phone call to the HQ and a simple request, we had the roughly 75 packets we request in no time at all. Exceptional and friendly service. 

You can also purchase cases of the bottled Del's should you prefer.

If you want quality sushi for a reasonable price, this is the place to go. They have a variety of different dishes to choose from, and i can assure you that you won't be disappointed. The staff are friendly, and the sushi is prepared within 10 minutes. I can recommend the grilled eel there, it's pretty good.
High quality sushi, very reasonable prices.
My favorite place to buy sushi. The space is very small so this is not a place to sit down and dine, but it's perfect for take away.

Compact restaurant, but cosy. Price is reasonable (at least in Norway). The staffs are very friendly. I saw people walk in and out, and they were greeted by the staffs, looks like they know their neighborhood customers pretty well. 
The only little down side is the tuna could be more fresh. I’m from Japan, it’s pretty easy to tell the freshness of your fish. 
Overall, not bad!
Probably the best sushi I have ever ate. Fresh and tasteful fish, reasonable price and very good sushi. If you are sushi lover and you are in Bergen - check it!

Family friendly, reasonably priced. There was a 10 minute wait. Beautiful decor. Looks like an upscale restaurant without the price tag. Staff was warm inviting. Our server was perfect. Food came fast and was delicious. I got the calamari entree and it was huge. Do not order appetizers. My kids loved their chicken parmigiana. Pasta was perfectly cooked. It was a great night out!

I went with a group and had reservations for 5pm. We were seated promptly, even though the restaurant was extremely busy and only became busier during our visit. The wait staff was very friendly and attentive. The food came out quickly and was delicious. I had the scallops casino and I can't say enough about how great it was. The portion was huge. Enough for another meal to take home. The parking lot is very big though was full when we arrived, but we were able to park on the street just fine. I don't know if reservations are allowed for smaller parties, but I would recommend them given the number of people waiting when we left at 7. I can't believe I lived in RI for 17 years and only now tried it after coming for a visit!

Brian our waiter was so nice, very attentive. But this time around my pasta dish the marinara sauce was very watery like the kitchen staff didnt drain the pasta enough. Brian brought me out more sauce which was delicious, after asking how he could make better, he was so nice. The seafood was cooked perfectly.  Usually  never had a problem

We arrived to a super long line spilling outside, but were able to get 2 seats at bar as soon as we checked in. My 1st visit here. The bar was fine for 2! The portions are huge! Definitely can split 1 meal between 2-3 people (easily)! My "super seafood special" with shrimp, (baby)scallops, and chopped clams over linguine with white clam sauce lacked salt, mostly tasted lots of butter, some garlic. Plenty of leftovers bc I hardly made a dent in it. Good place if you want leftovers. The women at the bar were friendly, hustling all night. My margarita was good.

I've been coming here for over 20 years and have never had a bad experience. Sometimes the wait can be long but definitely worth it. The food is always good, I love their lasagna. The portions are very generous so I always bring something home. The wait staff is excellent. It's one of my favorite places to eat.

Imagine fighting your way through winter storm, 100 km on foot. You had to fight your way through a pack of savage penguins and their boss leader, the polar bear, to the bitter end. You open the door after all your struggle into an oasis ice cream, awful awfuls, and traditional American fare. You think you were safe...but in the shadows a monster lurks. You let your guard down, and you order your food happy and content ...but the feeling that something is watching you slowly creeps down your spine. The monster exposes itself as a manager that has an attitude of the most heinous creature in all the land. Your Oasis is ruined... On top of this they have some how figured out how to take flavor out of food and replace it with salt/grease.

This was basically my experience with this Newport creamery. The ice cream was good but the manager at this location it's probably the worst person in customer service I've ever experienced in New England... You can tell the staff is unorganized because of her toxic leadership. I strongly recommend restructuring your management group to better facilitate a well running and friendly staff.

2 stars for quality ice cream though...
Slow staff,  burger was overcooked and dry fries were cold.  Manager did not care.  Will never come here again.

Newport Creamery is a decent place with average food but good people.  We go there mainly for breakfast because it's local, fast, hot, inexpensive, and filling.  That being said, the quality of ingredients is average, not bad but not impressive.  Basically it's an ice cream shop with a diner attached, that de-emphasized their ice cream.  IMHO, they are doing too many things to do anything really well.  It's decent enough food at a decent price, and you can take the kids.
Had our first Big Beef the Creamery Way in over 16 yes & it was like really coming home, DELISH!!
Always great! Servers are wonderful.

Went inside and ordered to go I waited over an hour for my food mind you customers that ordered after me got there food before me I had to be some where so I asked for my money back they kept telling me a few more minutes then the wings where done and still had to wait for fries I asked for my money back and he acted like he did not want to give it to me asked if I wanted a credit for the next time I came back lol. PS "THE STEAK SANDWICHES SUCK"

YOUR 'LARGE' GRINDERS ARE NOT LARGE. THEY ARE AT BEST SMALLISH MEDIUMS... THEY TASTED GREAT BUT VERY CHEAP ON THE MEAT, I CAN GET THAT SIZE SANDWICH ACROSS THE STREET AT SUBWAY. THE KID AT THE CASH REGISTER LOOKS PERPLEXED AND WHISPERS WHEN HE SPEAKS TO YOU
the service was phenomenal one of the employees Fernando, made me feel like i was at home and he was hilarious
Great food and services was quick .. love it!
Horrible

I happen to be a wicked famous person here in Boston.  I like Spikes. I was there when it opened. I eat the junk yard dogs. Chili fries are good too.  The place is like wicked clean too.  They got their own root beer and stuff. Five stars mates

I used to stop here as a young twenty something after the bars. Always loved the staff, atmosphere and most of all the dogs. Menu is more than hot dogs but with so many custom dogs on the menu I don't think I ever tried anything else.  I have since moved away and grown older...... today while in town I could not resist a junkyard dog. Went with my favorite the Texas ranger dog with fries. It did not disappoint.  Even after all these years and hyped expectations it tasted so good,still my favorite dog. Ps the Fries are good to. Thanks Dave!
Great local hotdogs, burgers and chicken shop. Fresh, tasty icon of Boston’s best. Driving by and stopped. Dave’s a personal friendly owner.
Spike s is my favorite place for gourmet hot dogs and chili fries.  I am like a wicked pissa famous person in Boston so I know where to go. Super friendly service and wicked clean too
Great customer service. And amazing cookies. Decent food
Oishii, 美味しい' , so delicious 🤤 This is the best thing that ever happened to RI.

Great place for sushi. It's the best place in RI as far as I and my family is concerned. Kids love to go there.

My critique is that if you're making a large order to go that it can take a while to get. Even if you get there when they estimate it to be done. It can be spotty. I would call in if you're not too far and see if your order is ready. I've had to wait for about 20-30 minutes for my order. They're great people and we think the service if you eat there is great. But the take out for large orders is what I'd caution you on. We usually do an order of $70-$110 now that the kids are growing up.

Have enjoyed all the food EXCEPT what they call tempura, simply awful. Tempura I have had everywhere else is always a very light Airy batter covered idem. Uncle Sushi tempura is a heavy crunchy bread crumb coating which is tasteless and a waste of money.
Love the sushi in here, small place but cozy and the food is sooo good and good price.

I have eaten at many Sushi places and after hearing how good Uncle Sushi is by my hair dresser and the reviews I have read I brought my grandson to Uncle Sushi and also took a spicy tuna roll to my son we all agreed that The  sushi was terrible.

If you want the best Sushi go to Itciban on Gansset Avenue Cranston you will never go to another Sushi place again.

Really delicious and quick! I got 2 hot dogs and sweet potato fries. The sweet potato fries were actually the best I've ever had! I asked for a cup of water and got a free bottled water, so that's pretty cool! Nothing bad to say!
Good restaurant. Went here with a big group and the wait time for the food shorter than I thought it would be. I do recommend if you get one all the way, it's pretty good even if your breath smells
Typical diner/wiener joint. Pieces are reasonable, service was quick, and the place was clean. The coffee milk was very good btw!

My husband loves getting burgers from here. I love the grilled cheese. They are very polite & make you comfortable as soon as you walk in. A few cons...They are a little pricey, and charge extra for lettuce and tomatoes on a burger. The tenders portion seemed to be for a child. And the hot chocolate is not good at all. It tasted like Swiss miss packet in very hot water, but there wasn't enough of the packet either so the turnout was a dirty water flavor! The drink cups are also on the small side for the price.
Really good. An offering you cant find elsewhere.  Only complaint ordered regular fries and got cheese fries.
Wow, great service, great food, and great environment. Fresh food prepared well. Steak was cooked perfect. Beers are cold. Worth the price and come back often.

I thought serving bison was a little gimmicky but I had the bison pot roast and it was good. Real home made mashed potatoes were good too. I thought the gravy was only so-so, probably made from a mix and not from scratch. The service was fair, did not understand the options for bread, etc, and didn't get served any bread at all. Which kind of sucked. May or may not eat there again or at another Ted's, done the bison thing and really don't need to repeat it.
The Waiter was cordial and professional. The quality of the Prime Rib was substandard. It was not edible. We have enjoyed other meals there but doubt that we will be returning.
Real, authentic, Midwestern cuisine. Truly captures the American spirit that this country needs more of. Go for the buffalo!
Great burgers. First time I had a bison burger and it was awesome.
Great Mexican food, by far the best we've found south of Providence. Good service, food comes out fast. Pretty cheap. What more could you want?

We love this place. Great food and awesome margaritas!  They bring you warm chips and 2 kinds of salsa. My kids love the tomato based one and the adults love the spicy one. Port Carnitas is our favorite dish to share. Yum!

Very disappointing and overpriced. Waitress had zero personality and therefore only got a 15% tip. She gave all of her attention to the table that was ordering rounds of very expensive drinks, of course! Fish tacos seriously should be renamed MUSH tacos...had to eat them with a fork. Tiny pieces of fish in the mush. Tasted just okay. Best thing we ate was the warm chips and salsa. We walked out the door with not as much as a thank you. Would never go back and I do not recommended. There was snow and ice to walk over outside their front entrance - definitely a liability and not wise on their part! Takes a lot for me to give a negative recommendation. Don't waste your hard-earned money. Too many other great restaurants in this area with grateful staff. Not this one!
Pretty good food, and the portions are pretty large. So far it's the best Mexican restaurant around I've been too
Good ambient and food but a bit spicy for my taste. For those who like spicy food and from scratch piña colada w/ a good punch of alcohol in it, this is your place.

I have been going here since 1990 and absolutely love their pastries. Their brownies are off the charts good! After moving away from Pawtucket I can definitely say I miss this place and it's so hard not to stop in whenever I'm back in the area.

They completely ruined my baby shower.. we gave them order to make cake and cup cake like week ago, and they didn’t made cake on my baby shower date..  they didn’t even bother to call us .. they are completely irresponsible.. 
if anyone want to order something from here, then think twice prior placing order..
Delicious pastries. Pizza strips are nothing to write about. Good bakery for a pinch
Always delicious and fresh. I got my zeppoles, line was huge but they were fast. all ready for us

I love this bakery i been going there for 30 yrs the quality of the food is FANTASTIC !!
MY FAVORITE is the maple frosted layered cake . it is a treat when i go there and surprise my daughters wirh thier favorite pastries .
Excellent quality meat. Good service. Crowded at lunch time because many people order sandwiches and wait for them to be made. I highly recommend Garden Hills Fruit & Deli.
A nice neighborhood store. I love their produce. Good meat prices and I love their chicken soup.
Awesome service and amazing fresh cut meat for grinders.  Highly recommend.
First time there and I will return. Huge loaded sandwiches. Well worth it. Best sandwich I've had in a while. Very informative staff as well.
Fresh made to order hot and cokd sandwiches. Huge selection of bread.

The first Mediterranean restaurant we visited after  moving to Rhode Island. The ambience, the food, and the people were amazing. My wife found and bought a Groupon coupon which is how we went, and would love to go back. I had a pistachio chicken item, while my wife ordered a shrimp pasta (I am bad at remembering specific names). Both were tasty, yet light. The rice and veggies were great. The coconut cake slice we had for dessert was delectable. But the real icing on the cake, was the Turkish coffee we ordered. One of the best and most flavorful coffee I have ever had (along with Cuban and Hawaiian coffee). The owner and the server were all very friendly and helpful.
This Efendi's Mediterranean Cafe & Bar is one of our favorite. Excellent food. Great customer service
Enjoyable food, that offer's up a full, expansive menu for Greek, and middle eastern cuisine. Flavorful, and worth a minimum of a few visits to get a full idea of the food served.
DID YOU HAVE FUN AMONDO?? WAS FOOD GOOD? DANCERS GOOD TOO?

This was my first time here and it was totally amazing. We ordered lamb kabobs and beef steak kabob with rice . Food was exceptionaly good and was cooked to perfect. Their service is totally amazing. Our server was a really pretty and cheerful girl who was too friendly and nice to slecet to from menu. And then owner specially came to each of the guest amd made sure everything os perfect. Definitely a great place to go if you are looking to taste authentic Mediterranean cuisne with exceptional service 👍

Stopped by here while driving through the area on a work trip. Great food. Lots of options. I had the turkey feta omelette which was delicious. Service was great, Andrew was super helpful. Overall, very good value!

My weekend Brunch staple. Took my niece here for the first time 2 weekends ago and she loved it. It’s always warm and inviting and I love how they updated the place. They are definitely great at keeping up with change. Thanks for your amazing eggs Benedict and your house blend coffee. I couldn’t imagine a Saturday without brunch at Ts 💕

Greatest place for breakfast, brunch or lunch. Friendly servers, wholesome food, nice sized portions. Ask for the mini bottles of real maple syrup for their pancakes, waffles, and french toast. For lunch get the homemade potato chips w your sandwich or wrap. Loved everything I've tried.

We had a family breakfast mid week and virtually at mid day.
T's is one of those popular places that always busy with guests coming and going for breakfast or lunch.
With creative selections to choose from they perhaps come as close as possible to satisfying all tastes at all times. 
From morning muffins to griddlecakes, egg sandwiches, and egg combo plates, to omelets and 
Eggs Benedict they're here prepared to serve you your hearts desire.
Great breakfast spot! We really enjoy the variety of different breakfast dishes they offer. Food is consistently cooked to our liking and the service has always been super.
I've been living in Providence for a few months now and finally have found a place for good Thai curry.  Best I've found in RI so far.
Really good ice cream and a wide variety of topics and a great location to!
Has gotten very expensive over the years.
Great ice cream and great location. It's a great place to get Ice cream on a summer night and walk around Pawtuxet Village by the water.
Great Ice Cream!  Plenty of flavors to choose from, sundaes, shakes, cones and dishes.  A little something for everyone.

People: please scroll down on their home page to the coupon.  Wish I could post the picture of it before they remove it.  They are fraudulent owners, not honoring their own advertisements.  To make it worse, they accuse the one who called them on it as being fraudulent.  Papas has my business!  There is a lot to be said for honesty and integrity!  Neither if which was displayed at Dear Hearts

A very nice breakfast/lunch restaurant. It was very clean and spacious. We had breakfast which was hot and tasty! Loved the homemade hash! The staff was super friendly. Excellent, extremely pleasant service, delicious food. We will definitely be returning for more!!

Don't know what happened but the quality of the food has dropped considerably...gave them the last three visits to get themselves back on track to no avail...too bad, because we were frequent customers...food overcooked and sometimes burnt...food arrived to table cold on last few visits...what happened to good ole pride in one work! We are moving on in the hopes of finding a good breakfast place.
Great food. Great service. Great prices. Cute little diner!

We walked in the restaurant and stood in the doorway waiting to be seated.  After a couple of waitresses walked by us with no acknowledgment, we went to sit at the counter.  Thankfully we were greeted by a friendly waitress who promptly took our order.  It was busy and we could over hear her say that she needed a tables food right now as it was taking a while.  We waited around 40 minutes for 2 orders, when we finally got our food my eggs benedict was cooked as if it were hard boiled eggs.  I sent it back and did not have it remade because I didn't have another 40 minutes to spare.  It seems as though they are short staffed in the kitchen and the staff that they have doesn't know how to poach an egg.  Thankfully the waitress was understanding and kindly took it off the tab.  If you're in a hurry don't go here.  Food absolutely not worth the wait.
Great food, service was fantastic,  very personal. Coffee cup was never empty.
The ice cream is good
Friendly welcoming server. Hard wrkr. All by herself with a huge line. Took the time to make our order correctly despite the rush. Ty

Been coming here for years with my kids and boyfriend. LOVE the staff--they're great every year! Delicious banana splits and soft serve! We came last around 9pm and we could kinda tell they were cleaning up so we felt a little bad but not after the line in back of us formed! 
Gonna keep coming back! Great service!!!
Traffic variety of flavors. The ice cream is delicious. I recommend a scoop of banana and a scoop of your favorite.
Cute little place for basic ice cream.  Nothing fancy or special but if you're looking for a quick treat this is a nice place to get it from.
